Google Data Analytics Capstone Project

Saad Ahmed Qureshi

2022-09-03

Objectives of analysis

  1. How do annual members and casual riders use Cyclistic bikes differently?

  2. Why would casual riders buy Cyclistic annual memberships?

  3. How can Cyclistic use digital media to influence casual riders to become members?

Business Task: How can the annual members be increased. What marketing strategy should be device to convert casual bike riders to annual members.

Data Preparation:

Link of the data is provided with the case stude and present on AWS server. I have downloaded previous 12 months data from 2021-08 to 2022-07 for my project. Data is present in quarterly and monthly format. I have used 12 months files and merge it to complete data. Since the data was provided by the Cyclistic company itself therefore we can consider it as reliable. Data is Reliable, Original, Comprehensive, Current and cited (ROCCC).

Installing required libraries

Setting working directory (where data is stored)

setwd("H:/Others/Google Capstone Project/Data/Combined Data")

Making combined files of 10 years having all the data form 2020-04 to 2022-07

All files have same data structure,; column names and valeus are unique

files <- list.files(pattern = ".csv")         
temp <- lapply(files, fread, sep=",", encoding = "UTF-8")
dt <- rbindlist(temp)

Data Cleaning Steps

Removing all rows where there is a blank in data, Only considering Complete Ride for analysis

Removing all blank rows where data type is numeric and developing new data frame

df <- dt[complete.cases(dt),]

Removing blanks from char datatype

df<-df[!(df$ride_id == ""),]
df<-df[!(df$rideable_type == ""),]
df<-df[!(df$start_station_name == ""),]
df<-df[!(df$start_station_id == ""),]
df<-df[!(df$end_station_name == ""),]
df<-df[!(df$end_station_id == ""),]

After cleaning 4629230 rows remaining, We can now proceed with out analysis on complete ride data frame.

Now we have to decide how to proceed further. Since I have a huge data (one year data 2021-08 to 2022-07)

Therefore, I am removing missing rows data from my analysis and only considering rides which has all the information as complete ride

Creating Variables for Analysis

Total Duration of ride

Creating variable of duration of ride with time format of HH:MM:SS as per the instructions

library(hms)
df$ride_length = as_hms(difftime(df$ended_at, df$started_at))

Day of ride

df$day_of_ride = weekdays(df$started_at)

Month of ride

df$month_of_ride = format(df$started_at,"%B")

yearh of ride

df$year_of_ride = year(df$started_at)

Creating Time of the day variable

Time of the day in 24 hour format

df$time_of_ride = format(as.POSIXct(df$started_at), format= "%HH")
